'''Herat''' was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Jawa/Legends|Jawa]] who was the [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]] of [[Wittin/Legends|Wittin's]] tribe. She was Wittin's advisor during his negotiations with [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]], and agreed to serve as one of Jabba's retainers as long as he helped Wittin. When [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] arrived at [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]], Herat was present and was retaining the [[Frog-dog/Legends|Frog-dog]], [[Buboicullaar/Legends|Buboicullaar]].

==Biography==
[[File:Herat_SWI_60.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Herat]]
After Jabba's death, Herat and her tribe were freed from servitude, and roamed the deserts of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] for many years. When they discovered [[Kitster Chanchani Banai]] in the deep desert, Herat agreed to transport him to [[Anchorhead/Legends|Anchorhead]]. The tribe was struck by two almost simultaneous attacks, one by an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] search party that was looking for the [[Killik Twilight]] moss painting, and then by a group of [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Sand people]]. Many of the tribe were killed, but Herat and Kitster managed to survive. Kitster was taken by the Sand people, and Herat was left for dead. She agreed to help [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] and her husband, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], locate Kitster and the moss-painting before the Imperials could, since her hatred of the Imperials had grown immeasurably after their attack. However, she was badly injured by in the attacks, and was forced to negotiate in return for treatment of her broken leg. She later came to understand the Solos' need to recover the painting, and agreed to let herself be "hijacked" in order to draw off Imperial pursuit. With the Solos' help, Herat got her [[Sandcrawler/Legends|sandcrawler]] working again, then locked herself in a toolbox while the sandcrawler was put in gear. The [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] pursuing them took the bait, and believed Herat's story of being captured and locked up after the Solos stole her cargo.

==Behind the scenes==
After [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket]], [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna]], and [[Ortugg]], Herat is perhaps the most minor of characters to appear on a Star Wars movie poster. She was played by [[Andrew Herd|Andy Herd]].<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://hollywoodshow.com/store/default/celebrity-merchandise/star-wars/andy-herd-star-wars-only-one.html|text=Andy Herd Star Wars **ONLY ONE**|nobackup=1}}</ref>

